CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1941 reads: "Mr. and Mrs. Earl Childs pictured after their marriage Tuesday evening in home of the bride's sister, Mrs. Kenneth De Honney, in Monticello street. (See Talk O' Town.) - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Romaine Trotman Jackson Childs wearing suit, large dark hat, brooch, and gardenia corsage, standing in front of fireplace in home of Mrs. Kenneth De Honney, 7242 Monticello Street
